Paperflite Automation Framework (Selenium + Java)

Overview

This project automates the end-to-end flow of Paperflite:

* Login
* Create Collection
* Upload Assets
* Generate Link
* Apply Gating (Email + Password)
* Validate in Incognito (Fliteview)
* Validate in Conversations
* Delete Conversation & Collection

---

Tech Stack

* Java
* Selenium WebDriver
* TestNG
* Maven
* Robot Class (File Upload)

---

Project Structure

src
 ├── main
 ├── test
 │   ├── java
 │   │   ├── pages
 │   │   ├── tests
 │   │   ├── utils
 │   ├── resources
 │       ├── Files
 │       ├── Data (testdata.csv)
```



▶️ How to Run

1. Clone the project
2. Open in Eclipse 
3. Run:

mvn clean test

▶️ Test Execution

Run using Maven

Run from IDE (Eclipse / IntelliJ)

1. Navigate to:

src/test/java/tests/E2ETest.java

2. Right click on:

E2ETest.java

3. Click:

Run As → TestNG Test
```

📊 Test Data (CSV)

```
collectionName,email,password,file1,file2,file3,file4
Auto_Collection_01,testuser@gmail.com,Test@123,Files/file1.pdf,Files/file2.pdf,Files/file3.pdf,Files/file4.pdf
```

---
Key Challenges Solved

* File upload using Robot class
* Handling dynamic UI (React-based)
* Duplicate DOM elements (carousel issue)
* Flaky click handling (retry + JS click)
* Incognito browser validation

---

Improvements

* Replace Robot with input[type='file']
* Add Extent Reports
* Parallel execution

